'''安娜·凯瑟琳·格林'''（{{lang|en|Anna Katharine Green}}，{{bd|1846年|11月11日|1935年|4月11日}}）是一位[[美国|美国]][[诗人|诗人]]和[[小说家|小说家]]，美国[[侦探小说|侦探小说]]开创者之一，以擅于写情节紧凑、滴水不漏的故事而著称。<ref name=obit/>格林也常被称为“侦探小说之母”。<ref>{{cite news |last= Penzler |first= Otto |authorlink=  |title= A Deadly Month |work= The New York Sun |location= New York |publisher= Ronald Weintraub |date= November 16, 2005|url= |accessdate= January 8, 2013 |quote= [Green] is frequently, inaccurately, described as the mother of the detective novel by virtue of having written ''The Leavenworth Case'', which is said to be the first mystery written by an American woman. But the honor rightfully belongs to Seeley Regester [1831-1885], with her 1866 novel ''The Dead Letter''.}}</ref>
